[Course_Description]
The Leader Habit offers an approach to leadership development that favors practice and habit learning over rote learning of knowledge. By looking at the ways habits are developed, and by breaking down the skills necessary for successful leadership into microbehaviors, author Martin Lanik offers a blueprint for becoming a better leader through short training exercises. This audio-only course summarizes the core components of the leader habit. Discover how to develop microbehaviors, keystone habits, and task-oriented skills and connect with your team through people-oriented leadership. These simple tips and techniques can help anyone become a better leader. Note: This audiobook summary was produced by Blinkist. We are pleased to host this content in our library.